Important Resources:
NOTE: Please understand the extrinsic and intrinsic properties.
Intrinsic : Properties that are constant. As this is somthing which is not going to change hence it is stored in the main memory
Extrinsic : Properties that are NOT constant and hence needs to be calculated on the FLY. As this is not constant, hence 
            not stored in the main memory. HENCE THE NAME FLYWEIGHT PATTERN

So a flyweight design pattern factors out all intrinsic duplicity 
- the shape/outline/black color - then the extrinsic (color fill) is calculated on the fly.  Right?ï»¿
Ans. YES

